Text.SourceString: Oh gosh. I keep running into you, Player. What a fun thing to happen.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh gosh. I keep running into you, Player. What a fun thing to happen.

Text.SourceString: What type of movies do you like?
Text.LocalizedString: What type of movies do you like?

Text.SourceString: Ah, I see... I’m too scared to watch thrillers. Suki held a thriller party where we all watched this movie about a mad man in a mask raging around with a chainsaw, and I had to sleep with my door open for two days.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, I see... I’m too scared to watch thrillers. Suki held a thriller party where we all watched this movie about a mad man in a mask raging around with a chainsaw, and I had to sleep with my door open for two days.

Text.SourceString: Oh yes! We should watch a stand-up comedian together sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh yes! We should watch a stand-up comedian together sometimes.

Text.SourceString: Ah, my kind of friend! I love romantic movies too. We should totally have a red velvet party and binge on them sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, my kind of friend! I love romantic movies too. We should totally have a red velvet party and binge on them sometimes.

Text.SourceString: That’s easy. Peonies, by far… They’re like the prettiest flower in the world, don’t you? Their blooms are so large, and the colors are blindingly vivid.
Text.LocalizedString: That’s easy. Peonies, by far… They’re like the prettiest flower in the world, don’t you? Their blooms are so large, and the colors are blindingly vivid.

Text.SourceString: Too bad peonies only bloom in the spring, though.
Text.LocalizedString: Too bad peonies only bloom in the spring, though.

Text.SourceString: Ugh... My room is such a mess right now. I should clean it up.
Text.LocalizedString: Ugh... My room is such a mess right now. I should clean it up.

Text.SourceString: No. Unless she needs to pick up some groceries, I rarely see Zarah in the shop. Not a big vegetable buyer either, it seems, 'cause I mostly see her buying a bunch of flour and oil.
Text.LocalizedString: No. Unless she needs to pick up some groceries, I rarely see Zarah in the shop. Not a big vegetable buyer either, it seems, 'cause I mostly see her buying a bunch of flour and oil.

Text.SourceString: I don’t really know Zarah that well but she she loves cookies, though. She buys them in bulk.

Text.LocalizedString: I love to read about traveling to see what the world is like, out there. Maybe one day I’ll go and visit them.

Text.SourceString: Maybe, maybe, maybe... With the never-ending bills, it's hard to know when that might be.

Text.SourceString: Why, of couse! I can bake more things, you know. Not just cookies and bread.

Text.SourceString: Hmm... Let's see. Pineapple upside-down cake, pumpkin pies, donut! Hmm... What else.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm... Let's see. Pineapple upside-down cake, pumpkin pies, donut! Hmm... What else.

Text.SourceString: Well, if I had to choose, cookies are probably my best-baked goods. I practically make them all the time, so I think that might have maxed out my cookie-baking skills.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, if I had to choose, cookies are probably my best-baked goods. I practically make them all the time, so I think that might have maxed out my cookie-baking skills.

Text.SourceString: Practice does make perfect. Maybe if Sam starts selling other things like pies, I can finally get good at baking pies too.
Text.LocalizedString: Practice does make perfect. Maybe if Sam starts selling other things like pies, I can finally get good at baking pies too.

Text.SourceString: I can't just start baking a whole bunch of cakes and pies at the inn. I mean, who is going to eat them?
Text.LocalizedString: I can't just start baking a whole bunch of cakes and pies at the inn. I mean, who is going to eat them?

Text.SourceString: Also, I don't want to buy the ingredients for pies that nobody will eat, only to get better at baking. Seems a tad wasteful to me.
Text.LocalizedString: Also, I don't want to buy the ingredients for pies that nobody will eat, only to get better at baking. Seems a tad wasteful to me.

Text.SourceString: Ugh... So much negativity. Sorry for attacking you like that, Player.
Text.LocalizedString: Ugh... So much negativity. Sorry for attacking you like that, Player.

Text.SourceString: Oh, Player! It's you again. How fun.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, Player! It's you again. How fun.

Text.SourceString: Tomorrow? Yeah, I think I’ll go and see Betty at the tavern. Why?
Text.LocalizedString: Tomorrow? Yeah, I think I’ll go and see Betty at the tavern. Why?

Text.SourceString: I haven't planned it yet.
Text.LocalizedString: I haven't planned it yet.

Text.SourceString: Oh, I don't think I'm ever this close to you...
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, I don't think I'm ever this close to you...

Text.SourceString: No no, it's okay. I don't mind... At all.
Text.LocalizedString: No no, it's okay. I don't mind... At all.

Text.SourceString: Well, thank you! It's my own creation, actually. I even worked on the batik of the fabric myself.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, thank you! It's my own creation, actually. I even worked on the batik of the fabric myself.

Text.SourceString: It took me a while to make this shirt. But the pattern is a pretty one, don't you think? It's all worth it in my book.
Text.LocalizedString: It took me a while to make this shirt. But the pattern is a pretty one, don't you think? It's all worth it in my book.

Text.SourceString: Oh, these bracelets? Not all of them are special. But like, some of them are. I just like wearing a bunch of them.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, these bracelets? Not all of them are special. But like, some of them are. I just like wearing a bunch of them.

Text.SourceString: Hmm… Let’s see. I got a couple of my bracelets from my best friends. They probably cost next to nothing, but they’re very special to me.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm… Let’s see. I got a couple of my bracelets from my best friends. They probably cost next to nothing, but they’re very special to me.

Text.SourceString: You can make so much with so little, once you have a kitchen. My trick is to scavenge, then make the harvest into a whole meal.
Text.LocalizedString: You can make so much with so little, once you have a kitchen. My trick is to scavenge, then make the harvest into a whole meal.

Text.SourceString: Aww, you poor thing. You must have a tiring week, huh? I wish I can come over to help out a bit… Take some weight off your shoulders.
Text.LocalizedString: Aww, you poor thing. You must have a tiring week, huh? I wish I can come over to help out a bit… Take some weight off your shoulders.

Text.SourceString: .. Maybe we both can just relax and watch TV together one of these days.
Text.LocalizedString: .. Maybe we both can just relax and watch TV together one of these days.

Text.SourceString: Don't underestimate the power of wild foods. You can gather them around the lake and make some pies or meals out of them.
Text.LocalizedString: Don't underestimate the power of wild foods. You can gather them around the lake and make some pies or meals out of them.

Text.SourceString: But you do need a kitchen. For me, I can just use the community kitchen at the inn… Unfortunately, I don't think it's for public use, though.
Text.LocalizedString: But you do need a kitchen. For me, I can just use the community kitchen at the inn… Unfortunately, I don't think it's for public use, though.

Text.SourceString: You're so brave and adventurous. We need to hang out more, and you must tell me all about your conquests.

Text.SourceString: Traveling conquests! Gosh. Hah hah... I'll bring the cookies.

Text.SourceString: Do you just walk for the sake of taking a walk? I always see you around the island.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you just walk for the sake of taking a walk? I always see you around the island.

Text.SourceString: Oops, sorry if that sounded harsh. I was admiring you, actually. Walking is a good habit to have.
Text.LocalizedString: Oops, sorry if that sounded harsh. I was admiring you, actually. Walking is a good habit to have.

Text.SourceString: I don't want to make this about me, but I really like talking to you.
Text.LocalizedString: I don't want to make this about me, but I really like talking to you.

Text.SourceString: You're always so... Kind to me. I feel appreciated.

Text.SourceString: Oh yeah, I work like usual tomorrow. Can't leave the bakery too often, or else we’ll start losing customers.

Text.SourceString: Umm... It must get pretty lonely up there, alone in your farm, huh? You poor thing.
Text.LocalizedString: Umm... It must get pretty lonely up there, alone in your farm, huh? You poor thing.

Text.SourceString: I live with a lot of people, and I still get pretty lonely sometimes. I can only imagine how hard it must be for you.
Text.LocalizedString: I live with a lot of people, and I still get pretty lonely sometimes. I can only imagine how hard it must be for you.

Text.SourceString: Oh good! I guess you're right. Not everyone is bothered by it.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh good! I guess you're right. Not everyone is bothered by it.

Text.SourceString: If Suki allows it, I would totally shelter strays in my room. But I don’t think she would be cool with that.
Text.LocalizedString: If Suki allows it, I would totally shelter strays in my room. But I don’t think she would be cool with that.

Text.SourceString: I don’t know for sure... I haven't brought it up to her yet. I’m a bit nervous that she might shut down the idea on my face.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know for sure... I haven't brought it up to her yet. I’m a bit nervous that she might shut down the idea on my face.

Text.SourceString: Oh! Stephen is different. He isn’t really loud or even the "walking around" type, you know. I think that's why Suki has no problem with him.

Text.SourceString: I don’t know if I can live in the middle of a farm, but I'm not crossing that out yet. Because who knows, I might like some space away from all these noises.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know if I can live in the middle of a farm, but I'm not crossing that out yet. Because who knows, I might like some space away from all these noises.

Text.SourceString: Thank you, you're so kind. I enjoy making clothes for my own personal use, but I'm not sure about making clothes for a living.
Text.LocalizedString: Thank you, you're so kind. I enjoy making clothes for my own personal use, but I'm not sure about making clothes for a living.

Text.SourceString: Do you really think I can sell these clothes?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you really think I can sell these clothes?

Text.SourceString: I lost a hat a long time ago and found it near the park, next to a snowman. I wonder how it got there.
Text.LocalizedString: I lost a hat a long time ago and found it near the park, next to a snowman. I wonder how it got there.

Text.SourceString: Ah, no. I couldn't wear the hat anymore. It went all soggy, and it lost its shape. Went straight to the trash. What a waste.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, no. I couldn't wear the hat anymore. It went all soggy, and it lost its shape. Went straight to the trash. What a waste.

Text.SourceString: I forgot what I was going to say... Sorry.
Text.LocalizedString: I forgot what I was going to say... Sorry.

Text.SourceString: Oh, right, sorry. Umm... I meant thanks. Out of habit, I guess. But you got me all nervous, so it's your fault. You should be apologizing. Hehe... No, please don't.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, right, sorry. Umm... I meant thanks. Out of habit, I guess. But you got me all nervous, so it's your fault. You should be apologizing. Hehe... No, please don't.

Text.SourceString: I stayed up late last night, thinking about you...
Text.LocalizedString: I stayed up late last night, thinking about you...

Text.SourceString: I'm sorry if that made you feel uncomfortable. I didn't mean it to be. For some reason, you have been in my mind a lot lately.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm sorry if that made you feel uncomfortable. I didn't mean it to be. For some reason, you have been in my mind a lot lately.

Text.SourceString: I gave Macy a beanie that I sewed for her birthday last year, but I have never seen her wearing it.
Text.LocalizedString: I gave Macy a beanie that I sewed for her birthday last year, but I have never seen her wearing it.

Text.SourceString: Do you think she doesn't like my present?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you think she doesn't like my present?

Text.SourceString: Yeah, I do always give her beanies, and she does have a lot in her room. So maybe she just has too many to choose from. Hmm...
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah, I do always give her beanies, and she does have a lot in her room. So maybe she just has too many to choose from. Hmm...

Text.SourceString: I have work tomorrow, but I’m free afterward. I’ll be at the tavern if you want to chat. Or we can meet up at the inn... You know, the tavern can get super crowded.
Text.LocalizedString: I have work tomorrow, but I’m free afterward. I’ll be at the tavern if you want to chat. Or we can meet up at the inn... You know, the tavern can get super crowded.

Text.SourceString: Beach isn't such a bad idea. Don't worry about the cold! We can always come inside... Umm... To my room or something.
Text.LocalizedString: Beach isn't such a bad idea. Don't worry about the cold! We can always come inside... Umm... To my room or something.

Text.SourceString: Totally! A day that I get to see my friends is a day well spent in my book. And um... I don't say this often, but you're one of them.
Text.LocalizedString: Totally! A day that I get to see my friends is a day well spent in my book. And um... I don't say this often, but you're one of them.

Text.SourceString: I hope you consider me a friend, too. Oh, I can't wait to hang out with you more.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope you consider me a friend, too. Oh, I can't wait to hang out with you more.

Text.SourceString: Are you reading anything good lately, Player?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you reading anything good lately, Player?

Text.SourceString: I’m not. I just see you at the library pretty often, so I assume that you're a big reader.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not. I just see you at the library pretty often, so I assume that you're a big reader.
